,"text":"The cord-like structure on the head might be a clue.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039057,0.083565,0.096524,0.10249,0.099347,0.097976,0.094282,0.087371,0.091694,0.078715,0.068001,0.060978],"unified_progress":[0.042167,0.073131,0.092278,0.11063,0.11008,0.10228,0.10021,0.091923,0.09103,0.075108,0.060235,0.050931]},{"section":9,"text":"Maybe a temporal artery?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03443,0.076469,0.093626,0.10088,0.10102,0.098185,0.096112,0.090944,0.090188,0.085389,0.071397,0.061363],"unified_progress":[0.042504,0.073956,0.091403,0.10438,0.106,0.1022,0.10137,0.09387,0.089453,0.080608,0.063619,0.050644]},{"section":10,"text":"Temporal arteritis, also known as giant cell arteritis (GCA), comes to mind.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033865,0.068908,0.083242,0.0962,0.10379,0.10405,0.10339,0.095524,0.085918,0.086387,0.070656,0.068069],"unified_progress":[0.038098,0.058663,0.080228,0.092746,0.098284,0.11596,0.10464,0.099478,0.092775,0.086603,0.072134,0.060383]},{"section":11,"text":"GCA typically affects people over 50, and the temporal artery is a common site.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03421,0.06923,0.081844,0.092949,0.10045,0.10344,0.10334,0.097265,0.089532,0.090656,0.073738,0.063344],"unified_progress":[0.060169,0.0702,0.081628,0.090675,0.095511,0.10122,0.099304,0.098515,0.091812,0.086442,0.069852,0.054671]},{"section":12,"text":"The \"thick cord\" could be an inflamed temporal artery.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039135,0.080797,0.090406,0.096028,0.095534,0.097061,0.095704,0.090026,0.096913,0.080688,0.071295,0.066413],"unified_progress":[0.045448,0.074285,0.091624,0.102,0.10561,0.10165,0.097811,0.092511,0.094019,0.075582,0.064018,0.055445]},{"section":13,"text":"Symptoms of GCA include headache, jaw claudication, scalp tenderness, and vision changes like blindness, wh